    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/climatological"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Any uncontrolled and non-prescribed combustion or burning of plants in a natural setting such as a forest, grassland, brush land or tundra, which consumes the nat ural fuels and spreadsbased on envi ronmental condi tions (e.g. , wind, topography) . Wildfires can be tri ggered by li ghtning or human actions.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Any uncontrolled and non-prescri bed combustion or burning of plants in a nat ural setting such as a forest, grassland, brush la nd or tundra, which consumes the nat ural fuels and spreadsbased on envi ronmental condi tions (e.g. , wind, topography) . Wildfires can be tri ggered by li ghtning or human actions.</skos:definition>
    <skos:narrower rdf:resource="https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/LandFire"/>
    <skos:narrower rdf:resource="https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/forestFire"/>
