    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/volcanicActivity"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Fine, less than 4 mm in diameter, unconsolidated volcanic debris blown into the atmosphere during an eruption. Can remain airborne for long periods of time and travel considerable distance from the source.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Fine (less than 4 mm in diameter)unconsolidated volcanic debris blown into the atmosphere during an eruption; can remain airborne for long periods of time and travel considerable distance from the source.</skos:definition>
